Activity Direction: Indicates direction of activity: inactive, decreasing, increasing.
Activity Qualifier: Indicates if AC50 is = to value or if it is infinite activity (i.e, inactive), >.
Qualified AC50: Qualified AC50; can be an IC50 or EC50.
Curve R2: R^2 fit value of curve. Closer to 1.0 equates to better Hill equation fit.
Data Type: NCGC designation for data stage: 'qHTS', 'qHTS Verification', 'Secondary Profiling'
Compound Type: NCGC designation for compound stage: 'NCGC Exploratory', 'NIHSMR', 'Compound Followup', 'Compound Verification', 'Probe Optimization'
Compound QC: NCGC comment on compound QC: 'DPI QC', 'NCGC Purified'
Data Analysis QC: NCGC comment on confidence of data: 'Curve Verfied', etc
NCGC Comment: Annotation/notes on a particular compound's data: e.g, 'cytotoxic', 'fluorescent artifact'
Curve Chi2f: Sqrt(X^2/f) of curve where X^2 is chi-squared. Lower number is a better fit.
Excluded Points: Individual points excluded from curve fitting.
Number of Points: Number of valid points used for fitting.
